article.description: Yale beats Dartmouth 81-66, extends win streak to 6
article.headline: Yale beats Dartmouth 81-66, extends win streak to 6
article.linkText: Yale beats Dartmouth 81-66, extends win streak to 6
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Jack Montague scored a career-high 19 points to help Yale extend its winning streak to six games with an 81-66 win over Dartmouth on Friday night. Montague, who came into the game leading the Ivy League in 3-point field goal percentage (.446), made 6 of 8 field goals, including 5 of 6 from behind the arc. Justin Sears added 16 points and Makai Mason scored 11 for Yale (16-6, 5-0 Ivy League), which started league play 5-0 for the first time since the official start of Ivy play in the 1956-57 season. Dartmouth (8-11, 1-4) made just 7 of 24 (29 percent) first-half field goal attempts and trailed 35-21 at the break. The Big Green pulled within nine on three occasions in the second half, the last of which came on Miles Wright's dunk with 11:44 left, but would get no closer. Wright led Dartmouth, which made just 12 of 22 (54.5 percent) free throws, with 20 points.
